    {
      "id": "sr-latch",
      "title": "Build an SR Latch",
      "instructions": "# SR Latch from NAND Gates\n\nAn SR latch is the simplest memory element. It uses two cross-coupled NAND gates to store one bit.\n\n## Goal\n\nBuild a circuit with:\n- Two inputs: **S** (set) and **R** (reset)\n- Two outputs: **Q** and **nQ** (active-low behavior)\n\n## How it works\n\n- When S=0, R=1: the latch **sets** (Q=1, nQ=0)\n- When S=1, R=0: the latch **resets** (Q=0, nQ=1)\n- When S=1, R=1: the latch **holds** its previous state\n- S=0, R=0 is the forbidden state (avoid it!)\n\n## Hint\n\nThe key is **cross-coupling**: each NAND gate's output feeds back into the other gate's input. Wire S into one gate and R into the other.",
      "palette": "nand-only",
      "startCircuit": null,
      "goalCircuit": {
