      "id": "gated-sr",
      "title": "Add Enable — Gated SR Latch",
      "instructions": "# Gated SR Latch\n\nThe basic SR latch responds to inputs at all times. In a real system, we need to control **when** the latch captures data.\n\n## Goal\n\nAdd an **Enable (E)** input that gates the S and R signals:\n- When E=1: the latch responds to S and R normally\n- When E=0: the latch **holds** regardless of S and R\n\n## How to build it\n\nAdd two more NAND gates in front of the SR latch. Each gate combines one data input (S or R) with the Enable signal. When E=0, both gating NANDs output 1, which is the hold condition for the SR latch.\n\n## Structure\n\n```\nS ─┐\n   NAND ─┐\nE ─┘     NAND ── Q\n    ┌── NAND\nE ─┐│\n   NAND ─┘\nR ─┘          nQ\n```",
      "palette": "nand-only",
      "startCircuit": "carry-forward",
      "goalCircuit": {
        "components": [
          {
            "id": "S",
            "type": "In",
            "props": {
              "label": "S",
              "Bits": 1
            },
            "layout": {
              "col": 0,
              "row": 0
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "R",
            "type": "In",
            "props": {
              "label": "R",
              "Bits": 1
            },
            "layout": {
              "col": 0,
              "row": 2
            }
          },
