    {
      "id": "edge-triggered",
      "title": "Chain Two Latches — Edge-Triggered D Flip-Flop",
      "instructions": "# Edge-Triggered D Flip-Flop\n\nA gated SR latch is **level-sensitive** — it passes data through whenever Enable is high. For reliable sequential circuits, we need **edge-triggered** behavior: capture data only at the moment the clock transitions.\n\n## Goal\n\nBuild a master-slave D flip-flop:\n- Input **D** (data) and **C** (clock)\n- Outputs **Q** and **nQ**\n- Q captures D on the **rising edge** of C\n\n## Architecture\n\n1. **Master latch**: A gated SR latch enabled when C=0 (inverted clock)\n2. **Slave latch**: A gated SR latch enabled when C=1\n3. **D to SR conversion**: D feeds the Set path, NOT(D) feeds the Reset path\n\nWhen C goes from 0→1:\n- Master was transparent (captured D), now locks\n- Slave opens and reads the master's stable output\n\n## Component count\n\nYou need: 8 NAND gates (4 per latch) + 2 NOT gates (one for clock inversion, one for D inversion) = 10 gates total.",
      "palette": {
        "preset": "nand-only",
        "add": [
          "Not"
        ]
      },
